article.headline: Toledo 83, Western Michigan 77
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keith Triplett scored 21 points and Keonta Howell pitched in 20 points off the bench to lead Toledo to an 83-77 victory over Western Michigan on Monday. Howell went 7-for-13 from the field in 22 minutes for the Rockets (9-9, 5-4 Mid-American Conference), who closed out the game with a 7-0 run. Justin Ingram added 12 points and seven rebounds. Ben Reed led Western Michigan (14-6, 7-3) with 21 points and Levi Rost finished with 17 points and seven boards. Rickey Willis made two free throws to give the Broncos a 77-76 lead with 2:04 left but Triplett then hit two from the line to get the lead back for Toledo. Florentino Valencia got loose for a layup to increase the lead to 80-77 with 21 seconds remaining, and the Rockets hit 3-of-4 from the line in final seconds to hold on. Valencia finished with 11 points and Kashif Payne had 10 points and seven assists for the Rockets, who improved to 6-0 at home. Western Michigan's Joe Reitz had 10 points.
